270
00:13:50,812 --> 00:13:52,635
Frank Jr. Jr.?

271
00:13:52,958 --> 00:13:56,000
You'd be getting a really good one.

272
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:58,448
He's really funny.

273
00:13:58,448 --> 00:14:02,469
Like, the other day, he made up this joke:

274
00:14:02,854 --> 00:14:04,333
What's green and says,

275
00:14:04,333 --> 00:14:06,198
"Hey, I'm a frog"?

276
00:14:07,417 --> 00:14:09,490
A talking frog.

277
00:14:12,135 --> 00:14:15,521
Oh, no, you can't have him, he's too funny.

278
00:14:16,187 --> 00:14:18,979
Well, all right, that's fine. What about Leslie?

279
00:14:19,031 --> 00:14:21,948
Oh, no, no, not Leslie. No.

280
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:23,354
She's the only one that knows

281
00:14:23,354 --> 00:14:25,302
how to burp the alphabet.

282
00:14:27,062 --> 00:14:28,479
All right, so that leaves Chandler.

283
00:14:28,479 --> 00:14:29,969
No, no, you can't have Chandler.

284
00:14:30,021 --> 00:14:32,552
No, no. She's my little genius.

285
00:14:32,604 --> 00:14:34,198
I got big hopes for her.

286
00:14:34,250 --> 00:14:38,010
She's gonna be a doctor or a realtor.

287
00:14:40,667 --> 00:14:44,427
Wow, Frank, I think we just ran out of kids.

288
00:14:46,010 --> 00:14:48,042
Oh, I think you're right.

289
00:14:51,042 --> 00:14:52,354
Oh, wow. Phoebe,

290
00:14:52,354 --> 00:14:55,958
I don't think I can give one of them up.

291
00:14:56,323 --> 00:14:58,479
I mean, you know, they drive me crazy,

292
00:14:58,479 --> 00:14:59,802
but they're my babies.

293
00:15:02,948 --> 00:15:04,615
I'm sorry, Frank,

294
00:15:04,615 --> 00:15:06,125
I didn't realize things were so bad.

295
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:08,115
You know, I'll help out more.

296
00:15:08,115 --> 00:15:10,187
I can baby-sit anytime you want.

297
00:15:10,240 --> 00:15:11,656
You name the day and I'll be there.

298
00:15:11,708 --> 00:15:12,948
How about tomorrow?

299
00:15:12,958 --> 00:15:13,885
Well, that's not good.

300
00:15:15,427 --> 00:15:18,760
But I can move some stuff around and I'll be there.

301
00:15:18,812 --> 00:15:21,135
You and Alice just take the whole day together.

302
00:15:21,729 --> 00:15:23,615
You'd do that for us?

303
00:15:23,667 --> 00:15:24,635
Are you kidding?

304
00:15:24,635 --> 00:15:26,021
That's what sisters are for.

305
00:15:32,073 --> 00:15:34,115
Oh, look at them.

306
00:15:35,823 --> 00:15:38,604
I love you so much.

307
00:15:39,375 --> 00:15:41,677
Oh, crap, don't wake up...

308
00:15:45,823 --> 00:15:47,375
Where are Bill and Colleen?

309
00:15:47,375 --> 00:15:49,104
They are in the kitchen, getting something to eat.

310
00:15:49,333 --> 00:15:50,854
Can you believe how nice they are?

311
00:15:50,906 --> 00:15:52,198
We have to leave.

312
00:15:53,906 --> 00:15:56,656
Why? What did you do in the bathroom?

313
00:15:57,281 --> 00:15:58,865
I didn't get to the bathroom.

314
00:15:58,875 --> 00:16:00,135
I bumped into Owen on the way.

315
00:16:00,187 --> 00:16:02,229
He didn't know he was adopted.

316
00:16:02,240 --> 00:16:03,104
There's a slight chance...

317
00:16:03,156 --> 00:16:04,708
...l may have told him.

318
00:16:05,240 --> 00:16:06,948
Oh, my God, where's my purse?

319
00:16:06,948 --> 00:16:08,802
No, I can replace everything in there.

320
00:16:08,854 --> 00:16:10,594
- Get that binder and let's go!  - Hi.

321
00:16:12,135 --> 00:16:14,427
Some little snacks for everybody.

322
00:16:14,479 --> 00:16:17,656
You don't have to eat the sour worms. Those are for Owen.

323
00:16:18,354 --> 00:16:19,729
I'll go get him in a second.

324
00:16:19,781 --> 00:16:21,250
By the way, you should know,

325
00:16:21,302 --> 00:16:23,375
we haven't told him he's adopted yet.

326
00:16:24,271 --> 00:16:26,021
But kids are so intuitive.

327
00:16:26,573 --> 00:16:28,958
Don't you think, on some level, he already knows?

328
00:16:29,010 --> 00:16:32,281
- I'm adopted?  - See? Intuitive.

329
00:16:33,042 --> 00:16:35,167
What? Where did you hear that?

330
00:16:35,365 --> 00:16:36,677
He told me.

331
00:16:38,385 --> 00:16:41,698
And he paid me 50 dollars not to tell.

332
00:16:42,687 --> 00:16:45,271
Which, technically, now you should give back.

333
00:16:48,385 --> 00:16:50,573
You told him he's adopted?

334
00:16:50,625 --> 00:16:51,510
I'm sorry.

335
00:16:51,510 --> 00:16:53,687
But You should have a sign out there or something.

336
00:16:53,687 --> 00:16:57,354
Or at least whisper it to people when they come in the door.

337
00:16:57,354 --> 00:16:58,896
"Owen doesn't know he's adopted,

338
00:16:58,896 --> 00:17:01,062
and he also thinks Santa is real."

339
00:17:01,062 --> 00:17:03,208
He isn't?

340
00:17:04,375 --> 00:17:06,854
We have to get out of here, baby.

341
00:17:09,896 --> 00:17:13,740
Everyone, I would like to make a toast...

342
00:17:13,792 --> 00:17:16,937
...to Rachel and Joey.

343
00:17:18,937 --> 00:17:22,156
And to love.

344
00:17:24,875 --> 00:17:26,625
Ah, love!

345
00:17:28,490 --> 00:17:30,854
L-O-V-E. Love.

346
00:17:31,417 --> 00:17:33,552
L is for "life."

347
00:17:33,604 --> 00:17:36,125
And what is life without love?

348
00:17:37,698 --> 00:17:39,562
Oh, my God, are we supposed to answer?

349
00:17:41,458 --> 00:17:44,854
O is for...

350
00:17:46,281 --> 00:17:47,719
"Oh, wow!"

351
00:17:51,156 --> 00:17:55,125
The V is for this...

352
00:17:55,177 --> 00:17:58,885
...very surprising turn of events...

353
00:17:59,781 --> 00:18:03,427
...which I am still fine with, by the way.

354
00:18:05,229 --> 00:18:06,437
E...

355
00:18:10,417 --> 00:18:12,104
...is for how...

356
00:18:12,562 --> 00:18:15,958
...extremely normal I find it...

357
00:18:16,469 --> 00:18:18,302
...that you two...

358
00:18:20,156 --> 00:18:21,635
...are together.

359
00:18:23,802 --> 00:18:27,104
And that one day you might get married...

360
00:18:29,823 --> 00:18:32,531
...and have children of your own.

361
00:18:37,208 --> 00:18:40,208
- Dude, are you okay? - Totally.

362
00:18:42,312 --> 00:18:43,990
Ross, you don't seem okay.

363
00:18:44,042 --> 00:18:44,990
I'm sorry,

364
00:18:44,990 --> 00:18:47,448
it must be the pressure of entertaining.

365
00:18:51,479 --> 00:18:54,812
I think everyone would feel better if we had some flan.

366
00:18:55,594 --> 00:18:59,385
Wait, Ross. Ross, l--I have to take off.

367
00:18:59,437 --> 00:19:01,312
- No!  - I'm sorry.

368
00:19:01,365 --> 00:19:03,646
I have an early class in the morning.

369
00:19:04,177 --> 00:19:07,583
But this has been lovely.

370
00:19:08,927 --> 00:19:13,156
Wasn't it? And you thought it would be awkward with Joey.

371
00:19:13,208 --> 00:19:15,771
And that you never really liked Rachel.

372
00:19:16,865 --> 00:19:18,417
You are on fire!

373
00:19:18,417 --> 00:19:21,521
I'll call you in the morning, okay?

374
00:19:21,573 --> 00:19:22,969
- Okay. - All right.

375
00:19:26,625 --> 00:19:28,750
God, Rachel, what Ross just said, that's just--

376
00:19:28,802 --> 00:19:31,094
That's okay. Girls tend not to like me.

377
00:19:32,271 --> 00:19:33,719
Fine.

378
00:19:36,312 --> 00:19:40,344
Okay. I guess it's just flan for three.

379
00:19:42,531 --> 00:19:43,937
Hey, that rhymes.

380
00:19:46,854 --> 00:19:50,365
You know what, Ross, I think we're gonna take off too.

381
00:19:51,552 --> 00:19:55,385
Of course. God, I'm so stupid.

382
00:19:55,437 --> 00:19:57,219
You guys are a couple now.

383
00:19:57,219 --> 00:19:59,667
I mean, you probably just want to be alone.

384
00:19:59,667 --> 00:20:01,604
No, it's just getting late--

385
00:20:01,604 --> 00:20:03,969
It's fine. It's totally fine.

386
00:20:03,969 --> 00:20:07,240
I've got plenty of margaritas. It's all good.

387
00:20:13,802 --> 00:20:15,906
I don't even know what that's for.

388
00:20:22,146 --> 00:20:24,146
You know what?

389
00:20:24,146 --> 00:20:27,333
I think I'm gonna stay here and make sure he's okay.

390
00:20:27,385 --> 00:20:29,490
That's probably a good idea.

391
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:30,646
I'll see you in the morning.

392
00:20:31,281 --> 00:20:32,198
Okay.

393
00:20:33,469 --> 00:20:35,125
Yeah, you know, Joey, l--

394
00:20:35,281 --> 00:20:36,937
I don't think he's ever gonna

395
00:20:36,937 --> 00:20:38,479
be okay with this.

396
00:20:38,479 --> 00:20:40,750
It doesn't look good, does it?

397
00:21:02,156 --> 00:21:03,406
Morning.

398
00:21:03,656 --> 00:21:06,208
- Here you go.  - Thanks.

399
00:21:06,969 --> 00:21:10,667
- Did you stay here all night?  - Yeah.

400
00:21:12,344 --> 00:21:15,458
So you took off my pants and shoes?

401
00:21:16,365 --> 00:21:17,708
No...

402
00:21:17,760 --> 00:21:19,271
You actually did that when you  were

403
00:21:19,323 --> 00:21:21,917
dancing to the <i>Chicago</i> soundtrack.

404
00:21:24,583 --> 00:21:27,281
Look, Ross...

405
00:21:27,885 --> 00:21:29,656
...about Rachel and l.

406
00:21:29,667 --> 00:21:31,437
Listen, you don't have to worry about that...

407
00:21:31,490 --> 00:21:33,469
...because nothing's gonna happen.

408
00:21:34,104 --> 00:21:35,448
What do you mean?

409
00:21:37,198 --> 00:21:38,760
She and I said from the beginning...

410
00:21:38,760 --> 00:21:40,198
...we weren't gonna do anything

411
00:21:40,198 --> 00:21:41,812
unless you were okay with it.

412
00:21:41,990 --> 00:21:43,542
And clearly--

413
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:46,490
What are you talking about? I'm fine.

414
00:21:47,292 --> 00:21:51,271
It's okay, Ross. You know, I totally understand.

415
00:21:51,323 --> 00:21:53,969
Of course you're not fine. You're...

416
00:21:55,875 --> 00:21:57,937
You're Ross and Rachel.

417
00:21:59,875 --> 00:22:01,646
Yeah, except we're not.

418
00:22:03,073 --> 00:22:06,187
I mean, we haven't been a couple in, like...

419
00:22:08,750 --> 00:22:10,750
...six years.

420
00:22:12,698 --> 00:22:15,208
My God, is that right?

421
00:22:16,573 --> 00:22:17,990
Has it been that long?

422
00:22:18,792 --> 00:22:20,510
That's what I hear, yeah.

423
00:22:22,646 --> 00:22:26,208
This is crazy.I mean, six years...

424
00:22:26,260 --> 00:22:29,990
...and because of me, you guys aren't gonna be together?

425
00:22:31,677 --> 00:22:33,187
Can I ask you something?

426
00:22:34,104 --> 00:22:35,323
Really...

427
00:22:36,448 --> 00:22:39,281
...what is this thing with you and Rachel?

428
00:22:41,354 --> 00:22:44,635
Come on, you know me. You know...

429
00:22:46,802 --> 00:22:47,687
Joey.

430
00:22:54,635 --> 00:22:56,406
I'm crazy about her.

431
00:23:02,271 --> 00:23:04,521
And she feels the same way?

432
00:23:07,198 --> 00:23:08,781
I think so.

433
00:23:11,979 --> 00:23:13,292
Well, then...

434
00:23:13,698 --> 00:23:16,156
...maybe it's time we all moved on.

435
00:23:16,917 --> 00:23:19,448
Yeah, but, Ross, I mean, you're not okay with it, so--

436
00:23:19,594 --> 00:23:23,104
No, but I want to be.

437
00:23:25,031 --> 00:23:26,479
I will be.

438
00:23:29,896 --> 00:23:32,594
Besides, I'm with Charlie, right?

439
00:23:33,021 --> 00:23:35,615
Oh, my God, I'm still with Charlie, aren't l?

440
00:23:35,667 --> 00:23:37,844
- She didn't see the dance, did she?  - No...

441
00:23:39,750 --> 00:23:42,833
No, that was--That was just for me.

442
00:23:47,323 --> 00:23:49,010
Hey, you...?

443
00:23:49,562 --> 00:23:51,198
You sure about this?

444
00:23:51,792 --> 00:23:53,760
Yeah, I'm sure.

445
00:23:56,917 --> 00:23:57,760
And...

446
00:23:59,219 --> 00:24:01,031
...we're okay?

447
00:24:13,729 --> 00:24:15,458
- Hey, Pheebs. - Hey.

448
00:24:15,458 --> 00:24:17,333
We just want to give you a heads up.

449
00:24:17,510 --> 00:24:19,479
- Bill and Colleen hate us.  - Why?

450
00:24:19,479 --> 00:24:20,990
Owen didn't know he's adopted

451
00:24:20,990 --> 00:24:22,229
and Monica told him.

452
00:24:22,229 --> 00:24:23,135
What?

453
00:24:23,708 --> 00:24:26,021
Still, he had to find out sometime.

454
00:24:26,073 --> 00:24:27,042
How would you like it

455
00:24:27,042 --> 00:24:28,198
if someone told the triplets

456
00:24:28,250 --> 00:24:30,000
that you gave birth to them?

457
00:24:35,250 --> 00:24:36,354
I'm gonna go tell Emma

458
00:24:36,354 --> 00:24:37,458
she was an accident.

